body: Several fixes regarding exports in UMD.<nl>See individual commits for more info.
title: fix(ngcc): fix UMD inline exports and re-exports
commit_message: fix(ngcc): correctly handle inline exports in UMD<nl><nl>This fix was part of a broader `ngtsc`/`ngcc` fix in 02bab8cf9 (see<nl>there for details). In 02bab8cf9, the fix was only applied to<nl>`CommonJsReflectionHost`, but it is equally applicable to<nl>`UmdReflectionHost`. Later in #34254, the fix was partially ported to<nl>`UmdReflectionHost` by fixing the `extractUmdReexports()` method.<nl><nl>This commit fully fixes `ngcc`'s handling of inline exports for code in<nl>UMD format.;fix(ngcc): recognize re-exports with `require()` calls in UMD<nl><nl>Previously, `UmdReflectionHost` would only recognize re-exports of the<nl>form `__export(someIdentifier)` and not `__export(require('...'))`.<nl>However, it is possible in some UMD variations to have the latter format<nl>as well. See discussion in https://github.com/angular/angular/pull/34254/files#r359515373<nl><nl>This commit adds support for re-export of the form<nl>`__export(require('...'))` in UMD.;refactor(ngcc): share code between `CommonJsReflectionHost` and `UmdReflectionHost`<nl><nl>While different, CommonJS and UMD have a lot in common regarding the<nl>their exports are constructed. Therefore, there was some code<nl>duplication between `CommonJsReflectionHost` and `UmdReflectionHost`.<nl><nl>This commit extracts some of the common bits into a separate file as<nl>helpers to allow reusing the code in both `ReflectionHost`s.

body: Get rid of the transparent intrinsics in the stdlib for optional-to-bool conversion and force-unwrapping optionals so we can generate simpler, non-memory code for these common operations.
title: Optional codegen improvements
commit_message: Remove the unused `isSome` Optional intrinsics.<nl><nl>We already have detailed knowledge of Optional's layout in SILGen, so these intrinsics were almost unused. They were only used in a few obscure places by some optional-to-bool conversions, used by 'is [A]' collection tests and the codegen for 'lazy' properties. Change these over to generate an EnumIsCaseExpr that we can directly lower to a 'select_enum' instruction in SILGen, leading to better codegen and obviating the need for these intrinsic functions.;SILGen: Drop '_unwrapped' intrinsics and use _diagnoseUnexpectedNilOptional.<nl><nl>Being generic, the '_unwrapped' intrinsics force trafficking through memory, and while they're transparent so always get inlined, we don't do memory promotion in -Onone. Emitting the branch inline lets loadable optionals stay values leading to better -Onone codegen. (It also lets us throw away a surprising amount of support code for these optional intrinsics.)

title: i18n - compile time inlining source map support
commit_message: feat(ivy): i18n - add source-map support to compile-time inliner<nl><nl>The inliner can now merge mappings for the translations into any source-map<nl>that was associated with the input source code file.<nl><nl>The merging is controlled by specifying a `SourceMapStrategy`:<nl><nl> * * `inline`: render the source map as a data URL in the source map.<nl> * * `external`: render the source map as a file with `.map` extension and write a comment to the<nl> *   source file referencing the map file.<nl> * * `hidden`: write the source map externally but do not add a comment to the source file.<nl> * * `inherit`: follow the strategy of the input source map.<nl> * * `none`: do not render a source map.<nl><nl> This can be passed to the `localize-translate` binary as a `--source-map` option.
